        "id": "e715e2a90a0d435a",
        "text": "In a recent dispute over the philosophical novelty of computer simulations, Humphreys (2009) argued in favor of four genuine philosophical issues that require the attention of philosophers, namely, epistemic opacity, the semantics of computer simulations, the temporal dynamics of computational processes and the distinction in principle/in practice. Of those four issues, this article focuses solely on epistemic opacity, arguably the most controversial issue raised by Humphreys."
